cs.GT, cs.CC, cs.DS, cs.AI, cs.DM 

This paper deals with the complexity of finding Nash equilibria in games, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT). The problem is shown to be complete in PPAD, which is a class of computational complexity theory (cs.CC). The paper also involves analyzing the structure of the game, which can be related to graph theory (cs.DS). Additionally, the use of approximation algorithms and the analysis of the exponential dependence on the number of players can be related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM), respectively.
